The paper focuses on the use of convolutional neural networks (CNN) for classification of Alzheimer's disease using MRI images, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of different CNN architectures and their comparison, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. Lastly, the paper addresses the issue of reproducibility and validation, which is relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
